Charlie Mulchrone (born 14 May 1989) is an English rugby union player currently playing for Harlequins in the Gallagher Premiership.
He first joined Rotherham Titans in the RFU Championship from Macclesfield RFC during the 2012-13 season. On 4 February 2014, he signed for Worcester Warriors from the 2014-15 season. On 5 April 2016, Mulchrone agrees a deal to join Premiership rivals Harlequins from the 2016-17 season.On 3 November 2017, Charlie Mulchrone was named as vice-captain in the first fifteen to face Saracens in the Anglo Welsh Cup. With most of Harlequins first team regulars being rested.
